        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 2:30PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 230 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boyero, or 33 miles southeast of Limon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boyero.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
